$ SAS programming - macro statement: %macro
@ %macro

The `%macro` statement is used to define a → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/macros[macro]. The definition of the macro is associated with the macro's name which follows: `%macro`:
code {
%macro TQ84;
  macro definition
  goes here.

  &→ Companies-Products/SAS/programming/macros/variables[macro_variables] are not resolved
  when the macro is compiled

  %macros are not executed when then
  macro is compiled.
%mend TQ84;
code }

The → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/compilation/macro-processor stores the definition in a → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/compilation/macro-catalog.

Everything outside of such a macro definition is referred to as → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/open-code.

sa:
  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/macros/statements

  → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/macros/using/
